```

In this updated example, instead of using the Q-Fab-Action, we have a Q-Button labeled "Open Form". On clicking this button, the `openForm` method is triggered and it sets the `showForm` variable to `true`, making the Q-Form visible. The rest of the logic remains the same, where the form is hidden when the `hideForm` method is called, and the form can be submitted via the Q-Button, which triggers the `submitForm` method.

To set the template to the top center, you can use the Quasar Flexbox grid classes. Here's an updated example:

```html
<template>
  <div class="q-pa-md q-gutter-md">
    <div class="q-mb-md q-flex justify-center">
      <q-btn label="Open Form" color="primary" @click="openForm" />
    </div>

    <q-form v-model="showForm" @hide="hideForm" class="q-mb-md">
      <!-- Form fields go here -->

      <div class="q-mt-md">
        <q-btn label="Submit" color="primary" @click="submitForm" />
      </div>
    </q-form>
